(4838, 'cpfc_rss_5a9aee0c825e26e858d1b3c8b16000866e15a691', 'a:10:{s:40:"92415bac6a12544690a609f4644d82c1f47aa749";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:32:"Preview: Leicester City v Palace";s:3:"url";s:79:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/preview-leicester-city-v-palace-2251852.aspx";s:7:"content";s:3042:"CLICK HERE to join the debate in the Leicester City v Crystal Palace fanzone ahead of this Barclays Premier League match.ABOUTLeicester are at the foot of the Barclays Premier League with two wins from their eleven home games and have been in this postion since defeat to QPR last year. Following a run of three matches unbeaten in the league, Pearson\'s men have suffered successive defeats against Stoke City and Manchester United, leaving them three points off safety at the bottom of the table. This weekend they face a side in Palace who have won four of their last five games under new boss Alan Pardew.The Foxes leading goal scorer this campaign has been Leonardo Ulloa, who has seven league goals to his name.Manager Nigel Pearson has made it clear this week of the importance of keeping minds on the immediate job in hand. "We need to try and keep a lid on how expectations and perceptions change. We still have catching up to do, we need to try and stay in contact. The pressure is always on us to improve those results."TEAM NEWSLeicester City :Deadline day signing Robert Huth serves the final match of his suspension but they do have Riyad Mahrez back from international duty.Two doubts for the Leicester boss are goalkeeper Kasper Schmeichel, with a foot injury, and striker Chris Wood has an ankle injury.\r\nCrystal Palace:Mile Jedinak has now returned from the Asian Cup tournament but misses out with an ankle injury and Yannick Bolasie is still away on international duty. Marouane Chamakh received a broken nose against Everton last weekend and a late decision will be made on his availability.MATCH OFFICIALSReferee: Lee MasonAssistants: D. England &amp; S BennettFourth Official: P BankesHEAD-TO-HEAD RECORDLeicester WinsDrawsPalace WinsLeague181417FA Cup113League Cup322Other100Total231722LAST MEETING AT THE KING POWER STADIUM27th October 2012Leicester City 1-2 Crystal PalacePremier LeagueA goal apiece from Crystal Palace\'s centre-backs ensured the Eagles\' picked up their first ever win at the King Power Stadium and extend their unbeaten run to 10 games as they moved to third in the Championship table.Lennie Lawrence and Curtis Fleming were once again at the helm and first-half goals from Damien Delaney and Peter Ramage ensured a positive end to a tumultuous week at Selhurst Park, despite a late consolation for the Foxes through Andy King.Watch highlights hereon Palace Player.TICKETSThis game is sold out.Please do not travel if you haven\'t purchased a ticket for the game. For more information on including travel directions, CLICK HEREto check out our away day guide.BETTINGLeicester to win: 5/4Draw: 9/4Crystal Palace to win: 11/5Odds courtesy of SkyBet.CLICK HEREto place your bets or sign up today to receive a free matched bet worth up to 30.LIVE COVERAGELive commentary of all 90 minutes from the match will be available on Palace Player. CLICK HEREto log in or sign up.You can also make predictions and debate the game at Sportlobster just CLICK HERE";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423230676;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Fri, 06 Feb 2015 13:51:16 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:68:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/leicester-v-cp-4-361-2229584_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-06 19:08:10";}s:40:"dd7f455f9f1720c20a3443b64ecafd7dffd37b20";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:24:"Leicester Away: Sold Out";s:3:"url";s:71:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/leicester-away-sold-out-2251912.aspx";s:7:"content";s:394:"A reminder that Saturday\'s away match at Leicester City is sold out for visiting supporters. There will be no further tickets available for Palace fans on the day at The King Power Stadium.Please do not make the journey to the stadium if you haven\'t purchased a ticket for the match.There will be live commentary of the game on our Palace Player service. CLICK HERE to login or subscribe.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423225180;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Fri, 06 Feb 2015 12:19:40 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:57:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/fans-4361-2096638_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-06 19:08:10";}s:40:"b08e54d2428a028f7974e74b62482df744a37f83";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:25:"Appiah Wins A Final Place";s:3:"url";s:73:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/appiah-wins-a-final-place-2252466.aspx";s:7:"content";s:1216:"A place in the final was secured by Ghana in a match that was marred by crowd trouble as they took the honours in this African Cup Of Nations contest against Equatorial Guinea.Kwesi Appiah played the full 90 minutes in a comfortable victory and had a hand in two of the goals. Just before the interval he won a penalty after being fouled by goalkeeper, Felipe Ovono.Jordan Ayew slotted home the spot kick and it was not long before the lead was increased with Wakaso Mubarak firing home from close range.Appiah was then involved in the third goal on 75 minutes as he did well to draw the goalkeeper out and then found Andre Ayew, who had an easy chance to finish for a third.With Ghanas passage through to the final confirmed Equatorial Guinea\'s fans\' started throwing missiles that meant rival fans had to seek shelter on the pitch around eight minutes from the end of normal time.After more than half an hour\'s interruption in play the match got back underway, but there was only three minutes remaining before the referee blew the final whistle.Ghana took their place in Sunday\'s final against Ivory Coast but unfortunately the night will be remembered for what happened off the pitch rather than on it. ";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423213236;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Fri, 06 Feb 2015 09:00:36 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:65:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/kwesi-appiah-4361-2252458_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-06 19:08:11";}s:40:"5a844ae1872d6e8edcbb8d425f11e9a360b785e1";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:21:"VIDEO: Lee Chung-yong";s:3:"url";s:76:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/lee-best-league-in-the-world-2250934.aspx";s:7:"content";s:1120:"On Monday evening the club completed the signing of Lee Chung-Yong from Bolton Wanderers and today the midfielder spoke to Palace TV and revealed his excitement at the move to Crystal Palace Football Club.This club plays in the best league in the world and it is where everyone wants to play. I am looking forward to the opportunity of doing that with my new club.At Bolton Lee played with former Eagles Dean Moxey and Neil Danns so the South Korean international is aware of what this club is about.We spoke about Palace as a club and they said how friendly it was and one big family. They also told me about the fans and how good they are.Lee is currently unavailable through an injury picked up in the opening game at the recent Asian Cup; we asked how his recovery was coming along.I cant join the team out in training at the moment but my injury is getting better and I hope I recover well and play soon.After speaking to us he went into the gym and did some work with the fitness team so hopefully it will not be too long before we see him action.WATCH THE FULL INTERVIEW&nbsp;";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423169708;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Thu, 05 Feb 2015 20:55:08 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:59:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/chung-43161-2250929_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-06 08:56:00";}s:40:"4698ca02b73f31545d5715335aa376b111b80a5c";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:21:"Bolasie: AFCON Latest";s:3:"url";s:68:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/bolasie-afcon-latest-2252281.aspx";s:7:"content";s:888:"Yannick Bolasie and his DR Congo side had to settle for a play-off game as they lost the semi-final encounter of the Africa Cup Of Nations against Ivory Coast.Yaya Toure put them ahead with a ferocious 20-yard shot but soon after Dieumerci Mbokani levelled with a penalty after Eric Bailly handled.Gervinho made it 2-1 when he curled in to finish off a breakaway and then Wilfried Kanon got on the end of a save from Serge Aurier\'s header to further extend the lead.Early in the second half saw a chance for Bolasie as he came close to bringing his side back into the game after a fine run and shot, but the chance went away and DR Congo couldnt get back into the contest.Ivory Coast will meet either Equatorial Guinea or Ghana in the final of the competition.Yannick will now play the losers of the other semi-final in Saturdays third and fourth place play-off match.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423146310;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Thu, 05 Feb 2015 14:25:10 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:69:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/bolasie-congo-2-4361-2220921_478x3591.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-06 19:08:12";}s:40:"592f385456c3c8427763556cf7e370118c817185";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:21:"The Reds Come To Town";s:3:"url";s:69:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/the-reds-come-to-town-2248816.aspx";s:7:"content";s:1248:"FA Cup 5th Round - Crystal Palace v LiverpoolThe above match will take place at Selhurst Park Stadium on Saturday 14th February 2015, kick-off 5.30pm.Tickets are priced as follows and are now on sale to season ticket holders and members. Season ticket holders seats that have not been purchased are now available for sale.A reminder that season tickets holders seats can be loaded onto their cards online. Simply select \'loaded to card\' option during the checkout phase when purchasing online. This opportunity will also be available to Season Ticket Holders phoning or to personal callers visiting the Box Office. Season Ticket holders who wish to purchase seats other than their regular seat should purchase in the normal way either online, selecting the e-ticket or paper ticket option, via the booking line or from the box office.The admission prices will be for all stands, (except Directors Box),: Adults 25, Concessions 15 (senior citizens &amp; aged 18- 21 students), Juniors (under 18\'s) 10.Members can purchase in the normal way either online via the booking line, or from the box office.CLICK HEREto become a member to purchase tickets and take advantage of some great benefits.CLICK HEREto book online.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423090224;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Wed, 04 Feb 2015 22:50:24 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:63:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/liverpool-6x461-2026112_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-05 07:58:25";}s:40:"f0a2311f5f36a3af75245423f0560e37cfd20510";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:33:"25-Man Premier League Squad Named";s:3:"url";s:66:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/25-man-squad-named-2248797.aspx";s:7:"content";s:822:"The club can confirm their 25-man squad for the remainder of the 2014/15 season has been submitted this afternoon.After a busy January transfer window, all four new signings have been added to the squad, as well as Glenn Murray who spent the first half of this season on loan at Reading.Players born on or after January 1st 1993 are classed as under-21 players and are therefore eligible to feature throughout the season despite not being named in the official 25-man squad.The full list is:Shola AmeobiYannick BolasieFraizer CampbellMarouane ChamakhScott DannDamien DelaneyDwight GayleAdlene GuediouraBrede HangelandWayne HennesseyMile JedinakMartin KellyChris KettingsLee Chung-YongJoe LedleyJames McArthurAdrian MariappaGlenn MurrayJordon MutchJason PuncheonPape SoureJulian SperoniJerome ThomasJoel WardWilfried Zaha";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423088331;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Wed, 04 Feb 2015 22:18:51 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:64:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/badge-2014-4x361-1962232_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-05 07:58:26";}s:40:"1487ebc3d0d8045895724b0c494519c949917277";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:41:"Season Ticket Seats Held Until 5pm Today ";s:3:"url";s:71:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/cup-tickets-now-on-sale-2235452.aspx";s:7:"content";s:1219:"FA Cup 5th Round - Crystal Palace v Liverpool or Bolton WanderersThe above match will take place at Selhurst Park Stadium on Saturday 14th February 2015, kick-off 5.30pm.Tickets are priced as follows and are now on sale to season ticket holders and members. A reminder that season tickets holders seats will be reserved until 5pm today and can be loaded onto their cards online. Simply select \'loaded to card\' option during the checkout phase when purchasing online. The admission prices will be for all stands, (except Directors Box),: Adults 25, Concessions 15 (senior citizens &amp; aged 18- 21 students), Juniors (under 18\'s) 10.This opportunity will also be available to Season Ticket Holders phoning or to personal callers visiting the Box Office. Season Ticket holders who wish to purchase seats other than their regular seat should purchase in the normal way either online, selecting the e-ticket or paper ticket option, via the booking line or from the box office.Members can purchase in the normal way either online via the booking line, or from the box office.CLICK HERE to become a member to purchase tickets and take advantage of some great benefits.CLICK HERE to book online.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1423046415;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Wed, 04 Feb 2015 10:40:15 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:61:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/facupdraw4361-2184637_478x359.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-04 13:42:11";}s:40:"87126a8be2e4606e974c1c8ffcad4112e6654093";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:39:"U21 Report: Crystal Palace 3-0 Millwall";s:3:"url";s:82:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/u21-report-crystal-palace-millwall-2246106.aspx";s:7:"content";s:2544:"Palaces development side returned to winning ways with a routine victory against Millwall at a snowy KNK Stadium, with new signing Keshi Anderson marking his debut with a goal.The 19-year-old had scored a hat-trick for Brentford in Palaces previous league game, and after coming on as a second half substitute he found the net to put the gloss on the victory over the Lions, with Fisayo Adarabioyo and Paddy McCarthy also getting on the scoresheet.After the pitch passed a couple of inspections after the previous nights cold snap, it took just four minutes for Palace to open the scoring with a well-worked goal. A brilliant first-time pass by Sonny Black found Adrian Mariappa on the right flank who whipped the ball into the box. Under pressure, Keaton Wood could only clear the ball into the path of Adarabioyo and the striker powered the ball under former Eagles youngster Tom King to open the scoring.The visitors then saw a goal ruled out for offside when Jamie Philpot headed home after Chris Kettings had pushed away a blast from Ben Thompson but was ruled offside, and Palace had a let-off when Angel Martinez was picked out unmarked at the back post but he screwed his volley well over.The chances dried up as both sides struggled to create anything on a bumpy surface due to the aftermath of the snow, with Mandela Egbo seeing a shot on the turn flash over the top as Gary Issotts side led at the interval.Four minutes after the restart the visitors were reduced to 10 men when captain Thompson was sent-off for a studs up challenge on Black, and with the advantage Palace doubled their lead just after the hour mark when Reise Allassanis corner was met at the near post by McCarthy who glanced the ball past King.It seemed to be a matter of how many goals Palace would score and Jacob Berkley-Agyepong went close in twice in quick succession when he was found by Allassani and forced King into a low stop, before putting the rebound over from a few yards out.But with 10 minutes to go they added a third when Mariappa linked up with Allassani and his cross was volleyed into the net by Anderson to register his first Palace goal and seal a derby day success for the under-21s.Palace: Kettings, Egbo (Magri 78), McCarthy, Hangeland, Mariappa, Allassani, Black, Boateng, Berkley-Agyepong, Ferrier (Dymond 74), Adarabioyo (Anderson 57). Subs not used:, Croll, Sow.Millwall: King, Siafa, Parr, Wood, Casey, Rylah (Farrell 51), Thompson, Martinez (Byron 61), Twardeh, Pavey, Philpot. Subs not used: Girling, Brown, Peter.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1422978720;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Tue, 03 Feb 2015 15:52:00 GMT";s:10:"localImage";s:65:"/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/adarabioyo-4361-2213231_478x35944.jpg";s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-03 17:36:47";}s:40:"2e605e5fd081173e7d59df6e0a2d6f42227bee50";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:30:"Gallery: Beckenham In The Snow";s:3:"url";s:77:"http://www.cpfc.co.uk/news/article/gallery-beckenham-in-the-snow-2247367.aspx";s:7:"content";s:159:"The snow fell on the Beckenham Training Ground this morning and we give you a chance to see some of the images taken at a cold training session for the lads.";s:9:"timestamp";i:1422983847;s:11:"publishDate";s:29:"Tue, 03 Feb 2015 17:17:27 GMT";s:10:"localImage";b:0;s:14:"cachedDateTime";s:20:"2015-Feb-04 10:32:47";}}', 'yes'),
